{{Year in Namibia|1980}}
'''1980 in Namibia''' refers to events that occurred in [[Namibia]] (also known as [[South West Africa]]) during 1980.
==Military== [[Operation Sceptic]] is launched during the [[South African Border War]] against [[South West Africa People's Organization|SWAPO]].
The [[South West African Territorial Force]], an auxiliary of the [[South African Defence Force]] (SADF), is formed on August 1. Conscription for all 18+ year old Namibians is put in place.<ref>[http://www.klausdierks.com/Chronology/122.htm 1980 in Namibia] klausdierks.com</ref>
==Politics== * 1 July: [[Cornelius Cloete]], a member of the [[Democratic Turnhalle Alliance of Namibia|Democratic Turnhalle Alliance]] (DTA), becomes the first [[Leaders of Namaland|leader]] of the newly founded [[Namaland]]. * 5 December: [[Thimoteus Tjamuaha]] replaces [[Kuaima Riruako]] as the [[Leaders of Hereroland|leader]] of [[Hereroland]]. * October: Rev. [[Cornelius Ndjoba]] resigns as leader of the DTA.
==Births== * 11 March: [[Beata Naigambo]] * 22 March: [[Sherwin Vries]] * 13 July: [[Jeremiah Baisako]] * 6 August: [[Paulus Ambunda]] * 9 August: [[Jurie van Tonder]] * 10 August: [[Riaan Walters]] * 13 August: [[Hilaria Johannes]] * 8 October: [[Günther von Hundelshausen]]
