{{Refimprove|date=July 2015}}
The '''Alliance PSD+PC''' ({{lang-ro|Alianța PSD+PC}}) was a center-left [[electoral alliance]] in [[Romania]] between 2008 and 2009.
==History==
===Formation=== In continuation with the 2004 [[National Union PSD+PUR]] alliance, the new alliance was founded in 2008 between the [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|Social Democratic Party]] (PSD) and the [[Conservative Party (Romania)|Conservative Party]] (PC), formerly ''Humanist Party of Romania'' (PUR) as a counterpart to the center-right [[Justice and Truth|Justice and Truth Alliance PNL-PD]].
===2008 and 2009 elections=== It took part in the [[Romanian legislative election, 2008|2008 general elections]] and in the [[European Parliament election, 2009 (Romania)|2009 European Parliament election]], with the alliance winning 11 seats, including one [[Conservative Party (Romania)|Conservatives']] candidate: [[George Sabin Cutaş]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.partidulconservator.ro/?a=1688 |title=Partidul Conservator &#124; Romania Valorilor: Credinta, Familie, Natiune |publisher=Partidulconservator.ro |date= |accessdate=2015-07-02}}</ref>
===Dissolution=== In late 2010, the Alliance dissolved, as [[Conservative Party (Romania)|Conservative Party]] joined the [[National Liberal Party (Romania)|National Liberal Party]] to form the [[Centre Right Alliance]] (ACD).
