{{Politics of the European Union mini}}
The '''Education, Youth, Culture and Sport Council''' (EYCS) is a configuration of the [[Council of the European Union]] <ref name="Council of the EU">{{cite web|url=http://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/council-eu/|title=The Council of the European Union - Consilium|website=www.consilium.europa.eu|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref> It meets three or four times a year, twice in its full configuration. This Council brings together the [[Minister (government)|ministers]] responsible for education, culture, youth, media, communication and sport of the [[EU member states]]. Its exact composition depends on the items on the agenda.

The Council configuration on Education, Youth, Culture and Sport was created by merging the former Education and Youth Council and the former Cultural and Audiovisual Council.<ref name="Decision of the Council">[http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2009:315:0046:0047:EN:PDF/ ]{{dead link|date=May 2017}}</ref>

The Council usually adopts recommendations in the field of education, culture, youth and sport. However, in some areas such as audiovisual policy or mutual recognition of diplomas, the Council can adopt legislative acts.

