'''Fehérgyarmat''' is a [[town]] in [[Szabolcs-Szatmár-Bereg]] county, in the [[Northern Great Plain]] [[region]] of eastern [[Hungary]].

==Geography==
It covers an [[area]] of {{Convert|52.46|km2|sqmi|0|abbr=on}} and has a [[population]] of 8089 people (2015).<ref name="HunStat2015"/>

===Twin towns — Sister cities===
{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in Hungary}}
Fehérgyarmat is [[Twin towns and sister cities|twinned]] with:

* {{flagicon|POL}} [[Nisko]] in [[Poland]]{{cn|date=May 2016}}
* {{flagicon|UKR}} [[Vynohradiv]] in [[Ukraine]]{{cn|date=May 2016}}

