{{Expand German|topic=struct|date=November 2011|Naturtheater Grötzingen }}
[[File:Luftbild Naturtheater Groetzingen.jpg|thumb|<center>Naturtheater Grötzingen</center>]]
'''Naturtheater Grötzingen ''' is a sylvan theatre in [[Grötzingen]], [[Baden-Württemberg]], [[Germany]]. It is a [[Thin-shell structure|thin]] [[concrete shell]] built in 1954 and seats an audience of 850. It was designed by architect Michael Balz and structural engineer [[Heinz Isler]].<ref>Tessa Maurer, Elizabeth O'Grady, Ellen Tung, [http://shells.princeton.edu/Grotz.html "Inverse Hanging Membrane: The Naturtheater Grötzingen"] ( 2013) ''Evolution of German Shells Forms: Efficiency of Form'', Princeton University  Dept. Civil and Environmental Engineering.</ref>

