{{infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = The Hangman's Daughter | title_orig = Die Henkerstochter | translator = Lee Chadeayne | image = | caption = | author = [[Oliver Pötzsch]] | illustrator = Ben Gibson | cover_artist = | country = [[Germany]] | language = [[German language|German]] | series = The Hangman's Daughter | genre = [[Historical novel]] | publisher = [[Ullstein Verlag|Ullstein Taschenbuch]] | release_date = 2008 | english_pub_date = 2010 | media_type = | pages = | isbn = | oclc = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''The Hangman's Daughter''''' (original title in {{lang-de|Die Henkerstochter}}) is a novel by [[Oliver Pötzsch]]. First published in Germany by [[Ullstein Verlag]] in 2008, it was translated into English and issued digitally under the [[AmazonCrossing]] [[imprint (trade name)|imprint]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://phx.corporate-ir.net/phoenix.zhtml?c=176060&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1428575 |title=Amazon Announces a Second Publishing Imprint Focused on Translating Foreign-Language Books into English |publisher=Phx.corporate-ir.net |date= |accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref> A paper edition was released in English by [[Houghton Mifflin Harcourt]] in 2010. The characters continue in the sequels ''The Dark Monk'' (2009) ({{lang-de|Die Henkerstochter und der schwarze Mönch}}), ''The Beggar King'' (2010) ({{lang-de|Die Henkerstochter und der König der Bettler}}), ''The Poisoned Pilgrim'' ({{lang-de|Der Hexer und die Henkerstochter}}) (2012), ''The Werewolf of Bamburg'' (2015) ({{lang-de|Die Henkerstochter und der Teufel von Bamberg}}) and ''The Play of Death'' (2017) ({{lang-de|Die Henkerstochter und das Spiel des Todes}}). The latest published novel in the series is ''The Council of Twelve'' (2018) ({{lang-de|Die Henkerstochter und der Rat der Zwölf}}).
The series had sold over 800,000 copies in all formats by the time the 4th title in the series was published in 2013.<ref name="TrachtenbergAmazon">{{cite news|last1=Trachtenberg|first1=Jeffrey|title=Amazon to Speed Up Authors' Royalty Payments|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424127887323415304578368591257874264|accessdate=15 August 2016|publisher=[[Wall Street Journal]]|date=18 March 2013}}</ref>
